      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the beef has browned, add your<strong> cornflour</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ginger paste</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>soy sauce </strong>and <strong>honey</strong>, then return the <strong>softened</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until sticky and the beef is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
